ferc_filing_data.tariff_title: Brush Cogeneration Partners Rate Schedule FERC No. 1

record_data.record_plain_text: RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1 1. Availability and Character of Service. Seller makes its electric energy and/or capacity available under this Rate Schedule for wholesale sales in Colorado in varying amounts, at varying levels of firmness or priorities of service, for varying periods of service, and in accordance with varying delivery schedules, all as agreed between Seller and the purchasers with whom Seller has contracted. 2. Applicability. This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of electric energy or capacity in Colorado by Seller that are: (a) subject to the Commission's jurisdiction; and (b) not otherwise subject to a particular Rate Schedule of Seller on file with the Commission. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between Seller and the purchaser. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established by agreement between Seller and the purchaser. 5. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller’s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller’s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller’s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. Sales under this tariff shall be limited to the State of Colorado. Seller has received: (i) waiver of the accounting and reporting requirements contained in C.F.R. Parts 41, 101, and 141 (with the exception of sections 141.14 and 141.15); (ii) waiver of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subparts B and C, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; and (iii) blanket authorization for the issuance of securities and the assumption of liabilities. See Brush Cogeneration Partners, Docket No. ER06-1543-000, at 3 (Nov. 30, 2006) (unpublished letter order). 7. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 1 seller in all regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. § 35.36(a).
